Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.52,0:25:28.01,Song,,0,0,0,,Off of Kuantan, on the Malay Peninsula,\NIt is sinking
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.64,0:25:30.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Prince of Wales sunk! \NPrince of Wales sunk!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.01,0:25:42.04,Song,,0,0,0,,It was you, our fearless and glorious Sea Eagles, \Nwho sunk the Repulse, who sunk the Prince of Wales
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.82,0:25:37.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Britain's pride, with which she intended to rule the waves, \NPrince of Wales is finally sunk!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.06,0:25:39.89,Default,,0,0,0,,No, we sunk it! {no clue}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.04,0:25:48.92,Song,,0,0,0,,Let us remember, let us remember\Nthis day for eternity {記憶せよ記憶せよ\Nいざ永遠にこの日を\N打ち向う敵艦を\N一挙屠り去りぬ\N開戦三日目に早この戦果ぞ\N沈むレパルス\N沈むプリンス・オブ・ウェールズ}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.60,0:25:45.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Who sank the unsinkable battleship?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.90,0:25:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It was us, the Imperial Navy!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.08,0:25:51.21,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right, it was our Naval Air Corps.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.92,0:25:55.72,Song,,0,0,0,,We wiped out the enemy warships \Nthat came our way in one fell swoop
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.21,0:25:54.76,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right, it was us—\Nthe Sea Eagles—who sank her! {海の荒鷲 - literally "wild eagles of the sea"; some other film translates it as "wings of the navy" but I don't think it's well known enough}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.76,0:26:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right, it was us—the Sea Eagles!\NThe Sea Eagles!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.72,0:26:02.86,Song,,0,0,0,,Three days into the war, and we're already victorious!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.86,0:26:09.64,Song,,0,0,0,,Sink, Repulse\NSink, Prince of Wales!
